Now I know why it is, now I can work on this. I found few people who understand this (beside from my partner and immediate family) and will bother to ask me stuff and with which I don't feel like I'm scared to lose them because of being annoying

Be normal or else they'll get angry and you won't even know why, they won't tell you and that'll be it. That's why I tried to achieve an unnatural perfectionism when it came to my behaviour. As if I was constantly walking over glass, I felt like I wanted to disappear

I lost the count of how many times someone called me annoying when I was a kid. The feel of my friends not liking me and don't even telling me what I did wrong was so triggering of my crisis. I spent days overthinking it, telling to myself to mask it better and be 'normal'

My failures hurt me a lot in every aspect, I'm not good as the rest so I need to work extra hard? That's not on me, now I know. When I knew I was talking too much or speaking my mind too much, hyperfixating with things I liked and only talking about it while annoying everyone too

Because there are expectations that are not made for us. Even tho I got good grades during my school years, I couldn't even control the fact that everything was pilling up and it was like my brain told me 'you still have time' (the due date was next morning! What?)

I also understand now it's not my fault and that, even tho the medication has helped me SO much, I wish the educative system could recognise neurodivergent individuals and not force us to learn in the same ways a neurotypical person does. We have more tendency to have depression

Since the end of the ADHD month is approaching I want to share some of my experience with this. I was diagnosed at 20 years old and it literally saved my life. For me it was finally understanding so many stuff
